docs.lead_paragraph: Like thousands of doctors across Illinois, Dr. Claudia M. Fegan refuses to take new Medicaid patients because her practice cannot survive on the fees Medicaid pays. Although Dr. Fegan's decision is strictly business, the effect it may have on medical care for the poor gnaws at her.

headline.main: As Medicaid Fees Push Doctors Out, Chicago Patients Find Fewer Choices
